org.modelio.api.modelio.model.scope

Class StereotypeSpecReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.modelio.api.modelio.model.scope.StereotypeSpecReader

  • public class StereotypeSpecReader
extends java.lang.Object
    Helper to find the stereotype from a stereotype specification as it is written in module.xml.

    The stereotype specification may have one of the following formats:

    • stereotype name
    • module name#stereotype name
    • module regex#stereotype name
    • module regex#stereotype regex

      • findStereotypeFromSpec

        public static Stereotype findStereotypeFromSpec(IModelingSession session,
                                                MClass metaclass,
                                                java.lang.String stereotypeSpec)
        Find the stereotype from a stereotype specification.

        The stereotype specification may have one of the following formats:

        • stereotype name
        • module name#stereotype name
        • module regex#stereotype name
        • module regex#stereotype regex
        Returns null if the specification is null or the stereotype is not found.
        Parameters:
        session - the modeling session
        metaclass - the metaclass to look from
        stereotypeSpec - the stereotype specification
        Returns:
        the found stereotype or null.
